76561198025495758,Recommended,294440,16076810,"Posted: 30 May, 2015",all,Fygment,"I remember playing the first shadowgate way back when it first came out in 1987.  I was only 4 years old at the time, playing it with my dad, but I remember it quite vividly.  My dad and I had a great time with all of the MacVenture games when I was a kid, and I was very excited when I heard about the remake more than 25 years later.The new version does not disappoint.   It has everything that was fun about the old ones, with much nicer graphics(though still definitely not AAA level, they are quite charming in their own way)  and new puzzles.  While it definitely pays homage to its predecessor this is not just a nostalgia trip; This is a very solid adventure game that stands on its own merit.  I would recommend it to any fans of the point and click genre, irrespective of age or whether you've played the old versions.One nice thing about this game compared to many other point and click games is that there are four distinct difficulty levels that  make major changes to what puzzles you will face.  This option makes the game accessible for novice/casual player while still providing a challenge for the most hardcore players.  Also, if you start on one of the lower difficulty levels, you can play again on a harder level and its almost like a whole new game, with all sorts of new items and puzzles.If you are not into point and click adventures you probably won't be into this, but if you do like this kind of game this is definitely one of the better ones."
