,Not Recommended,294440,13967181,"Posted: 13 January, 2015",all,Kuehnau,"I hate to do this, because I grew up with the classic Shadowgate on the NES and loved it, but this game just isn't as ""good"" as the classic.When I first saw this in the store, I thought that it was going to be a remastery with better graphics and some of the more obtuse puzzles refined to the point where they make more sense.What they actually did was re-imagine most of the entire game, changed a ton of the puzzles, changed how a bunch of them worked and put in a LOT of back tracking into the game.The classic game already had a standard ""timer"" with the torches that didn't allow you drag your feet all day, but it was spaced out enough to the point where the system was ""fair"". Not only does this game still have that timer, but worse, they enforce a mandatory curse that will end your game every time unless you can solve it. I don't know what they were thinking, but it was not an intelligent design decision.Let me tell you something, when your biggest selling point is the nostalgia your game generates, the last thing you want to do is change the game so much it is no longer recognizable.This isn't Shadowgate and frankly I am offended by what the developers did here. They ruined this game. I hope they NEVER get around to working on any of the other classic titles or they'll most likely just ruin that as well."
