,Recommended,294440,28198781,"Posted: 4 December, 2016",all,General Brent,"I will start off by saying that Shadowgate(2014) was the main reason I even opened up a Steam account. I played Shadowgate on NES back in the mid-2000s decade, as I had never played it as a kid. As far as point and click adventures go, it's certainly one of the best ever, and this remake does not disappoint. The atmosphere, enhanced graphics, well told story, remixed music, different difficulty modes, and varied puzzles and paths make this one outshine the original version even. With various customization options, anyone who enjoys point and click adventure titles will feel right at home with Shadowgate.For the best experience during gameplay, I like to set the music to retro 8-bit style and play that way. That music when the torch is about to run out always puts me on edge, and heightens the foreboding mood that a game like this is supposed to have. Some of the puzzles are the same as the original- such as needing to grab a shield to block the dragon's flame in the treasure room- but others require slightly different approaches than the original game, especially on Master difficulty. If you don't use a walkthrough, it will take quite some time to get through the game. Beyond that, I am certainly not going to spoil anything, so try it and find out for yourself.Overall, I highly recommend Shadowgate(2014). It truly is one of the definitive point and click adventure games around."
